#summary Reassigning troops in Power Bot. This feature works similar to the Transport feature.  It is handy when you have a city you don’t want to hose certain troops in.  Let’s say I have a city that is barely supporting archers only, but ou want to build as many ballistae as you can, but you want them moved to another city as soon as they come “out of the oven,” you would use this feature to automatically reassign them to where ever you want.

Setting up your Route

Click BOT, Click Reassign
Select your “City From” for the troops you want to move.  
Select your “City To” box for the city your troops will move to.
Find the troop you want to move in the pictures below.
Check mark the troops you want to keep
•	In the value field type in the amount you want to keep.  If you want to move them all, enter a value of 0
After all troops are selected to KEEP, then 
Click Add Route
Click Reassign = OFF to Reassign = ON

Close BOT

Deleting a Route.  
So you changed your mind and no longer want to move troops automatically for whatever reason.  

Click BOT, Click Reassign
Click Reassign = On to Reassign = OFF

To permanently remove the route
Click Show Routes
Delete whatever route you desire to delete.

Take note that whenever you port your target city you have to delete the route and readd them again to your target city's new coordinates.

